Problem Statement

Develop a Java application using an interface to implement different online payment methods. Create an interface named Payment with a method called pay(). 
Implement the interface using different payment service classes and display the payment details.
import java.util.*
interface Payment {

    void pay();

}

class GooglePay implements Payment {

    String customerName = "Raghul";
    int amount = 750;

    public void pay() {

        System.out.println("Payment Method : Google Pay");
        System.out.println("Customer Name  : " + customerName);
        System.out.println("Amount         : Rs." + amount);
        System.out.println("Payment Status : Successful");

    }
}

class PhonePe implements Payment {

    String customerName = "Raghul";
    int amount = 500;

    public void pay() {

        System.out.println("Payment Method : PhonePe");
        System.out.println("Customer Name  : " + customerName);
        System.out.println("Amount         : Rs." + amount);
        System.out.println("Payment Status : Successful");

    }
}

public class OnlinePayment {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Payment p;

        p = new GooglePay();
        p.pay();

        System.out.println();

        p = new PhonePe();
        p.pay();

    }
}
